AXIOM FRONTEND SPECIFICATIONS (apps/frontend)

1. Vision

This is not a "website." It is a Mission Control Dashboard.
The aesthetic should be: Dark Mode, Data-Dense, Engineering-First. (Think SpaceX Dashboard or Bloomberg Terminal).

2. Tech Stack

Framework: Next.js 14 (App Router).

UI Library: Tailwind CSS + Shadcn/UI (for robust, accessible components).

Charts: Recharts (for Analytics visualization).

Icons: Lucide React or FontAwesome.

3. Site Map & Functionality

A. Command Center (/dashboard)

Header: System Status (Green/Red indicator based on backend health).

KPI Cards:

"Booked Calls (Yesterday)"

"Active Experiments"

"KB Version"

Action Panel:

"Manual Run" Button: Calls POST /api/run/manual.

"Force Sync" Button.

B. Knowledge Base Manager (/kb-manager)

Purpose: Interface to view and update the "Contracts" (01-KB).

Feature: Schema Validator:

User drags & drops a JSON file.

Frontend validates it against the Zod Schema (shared or mirrored).

If valid, uploads to Backend.

Visualizer: A read-only view of the current active Brand Rules and ICP Segments.

C. Analytics Deep Dive (/analytics)

Table View: List of all Content Variants generated.

Columns: Variant ID | ICP | Offer | Replies | Booked Calls | Status (Active/Killed).

Filter: "Show Winners Only".

4. Architecture Details

src/lib/api.ts: Centralized API client. All fetches must go through this typed layer.

src/components/ui/: Reusable atoms (Buttons, Cards, Inputs).

src/app/layout.tsx: Global layout with Sidebar navigation.

5. Design Guidelines

Background: Slate-950 (#020617).

Accents: Blue-500 (Primary), Red-500 (Destructive/Error), Amber-500 (Warning).

Typography: Inter (Sans) and Fira Code (Monospace for IDs and JSON).